question: The "Wadden Sea National Park" is located in which country?
explanation: Wadden Sea National Park is located in Denmark. It is a Ramsar Wetland and UNESCO World Heritage Ste. It is located in the Danish part of the Wadden Sea. It hosts several migratory birds such as European Starlings, also various fish and invertebrates such as starfish and blue mussels. It is also a birds sanctuary and a wildlife sanctuary.
